snippet.textDisplay: I love the concept of this song! I don't understand why stupid people can't see the meaning behind this? But it they are too stupid I can't help them. "when you're with me no judgement" (you can also be yourself) you can get that from anyone else. (Because your/we're already judged. You don't have to prove nothing (I love you just the way you are) you can just be yourself (I'll never try to change you) when you're with me no judgement. (Loving you is taking you as you are) We can get that from everyone else. (I don't give a fuck about what anyone says, I love you and I'm in this with you no matter what). Niall? I think hearing that personally would be much more effective. I get it! Did you even take anything I've said to you into consideration at all? I know I'm just someone out of millions of no ones, but just please don't give up on them, and don't loose that it won't ever happen because it will. I just wish men wouldn't so pigheaded, and stubborn! Now is the best time you both should be living and loving each other and I can't figure out why the dots aren't connecting. Don't put off what you can do today for tomorrow, because tomorrow isn't promised. Me grandma said that all the time before she past away. But I so understand what she meant now! Today, as it relates to the present. We tend to procrastinate, all of us do that, we'll get to it tomorrow, or next week, or whenever I can, bit tomorrow never comes. I don't want that for either of you at all. Just think about it please? And I asked a browned eye person to listen to this song as well. We'll see what happens, just be patient please? Also have YOU listen to a song called flames? Quite an interesting song, please have a listen? Cheers!
